    "name": "NIR Sandbox",
    "description": "## About this Collection\n\nEach Postman \"request\" corresponds to an endpoint on NIR, and a selection of examples have been provided for each of them. Each example request is accompanied by an expected response.\n\n## NIR Sandbox\n\nThe NIR Sandbox does not require MTLS or WS-Security headers (as opposed to the strict security requirements in place on the Live environment).\n\nAll test data and downstream systems are provided using mocks and simulators.\n\n## Examples\n\nTest data has been set up to demonstrate the following scenarios:\n\n| **Scenario** | **Simulator 1 -** urn:oid:1.2.34.567.8.1 | Simulator 2 - urn:oid:1.2.34.567.8.2 | Postman Collection Example |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Query a single document for a single patient from a single network | Patient Id: 9694116422 |  | Single Document From A Single Network (PDF) |\n| Query multiple documents for a single patient from a single network | Patient Id: 9898841141 |  | Multiple Documents From A Single Network (PDF, DICOM) |\n| Query multiple documents for a single patient across multiple network | Patient Id: 9932549118 | Patient Id: 9932549118 | Documents From Multiple Networks (PDF, DICOM) |\n| Retrieve a single document from a single network | Patient Id: 9932549118  <br>  <br>Repository Id: 1.1.4567332.1.7  <br>  <br>Document Id: 1.2.42.20251212161454.4 | Patient Id: 9932549118  <br>  <br>Repository Id: 1.1.4567332.1.2  <br>  <br>Document Id: 2.25.90214658647374166344513344800740950001 | Single Document From A Single Network (TEXT) (Simulator 1)  <br>  <br>Single Document From A Single Network (DICOM) (Simulator 2) |\n| Retrieve multiple documents from a single network | Patient Id: 9898841141  <br>  <br>Repository Id: 1.1.4567332.1.7  <br>  <br>Document 1 Id: 2.25.90214658647374166344513344800740950001  <br>  <br>Document 2 Id: 1.2.42.20260115152435.2 |  | Multiple Documents From a Single Network - Document 1 (DICOM)  <br>  <br>Multiple Documents From a Single Network - Document 2 (PDF) |\n\n  \nAdditional examples for Cross Gateway Query:\n\n- No Documents Registered\n    \n- No Matching Patient Id\n    \n- Error - Invalid Patient Id\n    \n- Error - Unsupported Availability Status\n    \n- Error - Unsupported Query Parameter\n    \n- Error - Invalid XML\n    \n\nAdditional examples for Cross Gateway Retrieve:\n\n- Error - Repository Id Not Found\n    \n- Error - Responding Gateway Not Found\n    \n- Error - Invalid XML",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "47493839",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/47493839-f740a09f-fcd6-44e9-9834-7ca34d83cbf0?source=collection_link"
